Two-time Milan marathon winner Titus Ekiru is the sports personality of the month for May. Ekiru improved the course record he set in 2019 of 2 hours 4 minutes and 46 seconds by 1 minute 49 seconds. He became the joint fifth fastest marathoner of all time. His winning time went into the records as the fastest time run in a marathon in May and an Italian all-comers record. Ekiru is now preparing for the Chicago marathon where he aims to break Kipchoge's record